We are deeply saddened by the passing of our friend Ashley Morrison (@youngestoldcatlady). Ashley had a welcoming personality, a great sense of humor, and a caring spirit. Our condolences go out to her friends and family.

If you are struggling with mental health, you are not alone. Please call the Suicide and Crisis Hotline at 988 (U.S.) or a similar crisis hotline in your country if you need someone to talk to.

If you would like to support an organization in memory of Ashley, her mom has suggested donating to a spay/neuter organization or the National Alliance on Mental Illness (NAMI).

The FINAL episode of The Purrrcast drops this Wednesday, January 10! A huge thank you to everyone who has made this podcast so much fun to do over the last eight and a half years - including all our ameowzing guests (and of course their cats), the @exactlyright network, our friends and family, and last but not least, YOU - for listening to the pod and supporting us! Oh - and of course, a big thank you to Samba, Tango, and Penny Lane for allowing us to tell their stories every week. We are so grateful for the hundreds of hours chatting cats with the best cat people and the many, many cats we've gotten to pet.

We have a very special guest for our last episode and can't wait for you all to hear it.

And as always... Fuck lilies!

Some photos from the very first recording of @thepurrrcast back in July 2015. We were both fine with it being a practice round or test, but we liked it so much we released it as our first episode. 441 episodes later, our last episode comes out tomorrow. What an incredible ride. ❤️❤️❤️

#thepurrrcast #podcasts #catsofinstagram

On episode 442 of The Purrrcast - our FINAL episode - we are honored to be joined by @hardstark to chat about Mimi, Dottie, @cookieandmoe. Thank you for making our last episode so special, Georgia. ❤️

Thank you, everyone, for your years of support! We love you and your cats!
